<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambicans Urged to Vote on Voting Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO September 15 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano has urged the people to vote in the country's second
democratic elections.
</P>
<P>
While addressing the residents of the district of Manica in
central Manica Province Tuesday, the president called on all the
people to vote when the time comes but reminded them that in order
to vote, one must register first, and that voter registration ends
this Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chissano asked the people not to respond with violence to
provocations by any political party during the election campaign
scheduled to start mid- October, the Mozambique News Agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the electoral campaign runs peacefully. Let no
one intimidate anyone else," the president was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Chissano warned his audience that when the election campaign
starts, there will be intense political activity across the
country, and that he will be visiting many places as the
presidential candidate of the ruling Mozambique Liberation Front
Party (Frelimo) to explain his party's plan for governance for the
next five years.
</P>
<P>
"Those who like me, and those who do not, should go and say so
by voting. Those who like me, should not be afraid because nobody
will know which way have they voted," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chissano refrained from making public his party's future plans
for governance, promising to do so during the election campaign.
</P>
<P>
He explained that he has been visiting various provinces and
districts during the past few weeks to hear what the people have
to say about the Frelimo government's record over the past five
years, and what they would like the future government to do as
priorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
