<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Communist Party Chief Raps Gov't Economic Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- National Secretary of the
French Communist Party (PCF) Robert Hue criticized Wednesday the
economic policy of the Socialist government of Prime Minister
Lionel Jospin, which he said is letting the market make the law.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with France Inter, Hue said it is "paradoxical
that the market continues to make the law while it is the
pluralist left who is running the country."
</P>
<P>
"A government of the left, a prime minister of the left, cannot
imagine not to find the answer, through the law, which will
prevent the market from crushing the economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
The PCF, which is part of the ruling leftwing coalition, is
particularly unhappy about the government's failure to oppose a
layoff plan by the automobile tire group Michelin to downsize by
one tenth its 75,000 working force in Europe in three years.
</P>
<P>
Hue proposed during the annual festival of the PCF daily
"Humanite" last weekend that a "great national manifestation" be
made against unemployment and for employment of all.
</P>
<P>
Jospin said last week that the government could no longer exert
an omnipresent power in the economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
