<HEADLINE> Lebanese Civilian Wounded in Israeli Shelling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese farmer was wounded
in Israeli shelling on a mountainous area in south Lebanon on
Wednesday, Lebanese security sources said.
</P>
<P>
Mohamad Akla, 65, was moderately hurt when Israeli warplanes
fired missles on the mountain near Labbaya just north of the
eastern sector of the Israel-occupying border zone in south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
There have been no apparent reasons for the Israeli air raids
which were the second in two days, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has been
launching rocket and heavy machinegun attacks nearly on a daily
basis on Israeli troops inside the border enclave.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 to protect its north from Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border
attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli troops out of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
