<HEADLINE> Senior Official: Better Trade Union Cadres Needed In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee, said today that there
needs to be better training for more better trade union cadres.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also president of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions, made the remark at a ceremony for the 50th anniversary of
the founding of the Chinese Workers' Movement Institute.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's reforms have entered a crucial period, a
time when new problems are popping up one by one. If trade unions
hope to play a role in China's reforms, they must have higher
quality cadres that are comfortable with the new situation and new
tasks, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wei said he hopes that the Institute will help train more of
these much-needed cadres for the country's trade unions.
</P>
<P>
The Institute is affiliated with the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions and has trained more than 70,000 trade union cadres
and other personnel.  
</P>
