<HEADLINE> Equity Prices in Greece Surge to Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Greek equity prices soared
to new records Wednesday with the general index on the Athens
Stock Exchange (ASE) jumping 2.10 percent to 6,181.05 points.
</P>
<P>
This is the ASE general index's 51st record this year, and it
now stands 125.79 percent higher since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index Wednesday also ended 0.76 percent higher
at 3,197.02 points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was more than 500 billion drachmas (about 1.6 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 266 to 37 with another six issues
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The construction and holding sectors led the rising stock
market, ending 6.60 percent and 5.86 percent higher respectively.
</P>
