<BODY>
<HEADLINE> MFC Bancorp to Provide Swiss Private Banking on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- MFC Bancorp Ltd. announced
Wednesday that it will provide Swiss Private Banking and Brokerage
services over the Internet through its wholly-owned subsidiary,
MFC Merchant Bank S.A.
</P>
<P>
The SwissNetBanking.com web site will offer investors the
opportunity to open a private Swiss bank account to trade
securities over the Internet beginning October 15, 1999, MFC said.
</P>
<P>
"MFC intends to be the first bank to offer small and
medium-sized investors the advantages of both Swiss private
banking and discounted brokerage services on a global basis
through the Internet," said Michael Smith, president of MFC
Bancorp Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Smith said, "Swiss banks are the largest offshore market in the
world, currently managing assets of approximately 1.5 trillion
U.S. dollars, which is 30 percent of the worldwide market for
international private banking."
</P>
<P>
"However, Switzerland, Europe and the rest of the world
significantly lag the U.S. in the development of Internet-based
discount stock brokerage services."
</P>
<P>
Peter Jessop, first vice president, MFC Merchant Bank S.A.,
said, "Our first trading services will be offered for stocks and
options traded on the U.S. exchanges. By the end of next year we
will offer trading facilities on the European, South &AMP; Latin
American, and Asian exchanges, and will provide concurrent
multilingual services."
</P>
<P>
MFC Bancorp Ltd. owns companies that operate in the financial
services industry, specializing in private and investment banking
internationally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
