<HEADLINE> Nairobi Opens 2nd International Book Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The 2nd Nairobi International
Book Fair with the theme of "A New Dawn in Reading" opened at the
Sairt Center in the Kenyan capital Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Attending the five-day fair are some 40 local and foreign
publishers, distributors and wholesalers from Tanzania, Uganda,
Britain, France and the U.N. agencies such as the Environment
Program (UNEP) and the Center for Human Settlements (Habitat).
</P>
<P>
Thousands of titles are being shown on the fair, including
academic journals and books, best-selling novels and literary
fiction, dictionaries, school textbooks, educational and cultural
books, children's picture and story books, wall maps and other
print materials and visual products.
</P>
<P>
The fair, organized by the Kenya Publishers Association, allows
the exhibitors to sell their books directly from their stands at
discounted prices as an incentive measure.
</P>
<P>
The highlights of the fair will include two workshops, one on
"Buying and Selling of Rights" and the other on "Recent Trends in
Creative Writing in Kenya", the organizer said.
</P>
<P>
The first such event was held in September last year and was
attended by 27 local publishers and several foreign organizations.
 
</P>
