<HEADLINE> Last Day of Strike in Bangladesh Passes Off Peacefully </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The last day of a three-day
hartal (general strike) sponsored by the Bangladesh Nationalist
Party (BNP)-led opposition alliance passed off almost peacefully
across the country.
</P>
<P>
Life was basically normal throughout the country, including the
capital city.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested 85 people in Dhaka on Wednesday during the
hartal for their alleged involvement in violence.
</P>
<P>
Different front organizations of the ruling Bangladesh Awami
League brought out anti-hartal processions and paraded different
city streets during the hartal hours.
</P>
<P>
Home, Post and Telecommunications Minister Mohammad Nasim
bitterly criticized the opposition for calling the three-day
hartal, saying that the opposition had tried to hold the people of
Dhaka city hostage by hurling bombs and creating panic.
</P>
<P>
The combined opposition declared a three-day hartal across the
country from Monday to demand the resignation of the government
and immediate parliamentary elections. 
</P>
