<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt is ready to host an international conference
next year to discuss Middle East economic cooperation, the
country's foreign minister has said in remarks published on the
Egyptian Gazette newspaper Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"There will be a possibility for Egypt to host the conference
next year after the revival of the Palestinian, Syrian and
Lebanese peace tracks," Amr Moussa told reporters Tuesday on the
fringes of an economic meeting in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Moussa was referring to the Middle East and North Africa (MENA)
Economic Conference aimed at boosting Arab-Israeli cooperation.
(BC-Egypt-MENA Conference)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- An Israeli computer amateur has found a solution
to the Year 2000 computer problem (Y2K) that is applicable to all
databases, a local newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Sapir 2000 program, developed by Ben-Etzion Yaron, head of
Manpower and Payroll Department in Hebrew University, compresses
four digits for the years in the 21st century into two symbols by
using special algorithms, so the code for any year in the 21st
century will not be the same as the year 100 years ago.
(BC-Israel-Y2K)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- The Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) on Wednesday
informed Turkey that it has allocated 400 million U.S. dollars in
reconstruction aid to the country following last month's killer
earthquake.
</P>
