<HEADLINE> UK Unemployment Figure At 19-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The number of people claiming
unemployment benefits in Britain fell by 22,300 in August to
1,211,500, according to the official figures released Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It is the sixth month in a row that the jobless total has
dropped. The claimant rate of 4.2 percent was the lowest since
February 1980. The Office for National Statistics said that
enemployment is still on a downward trend.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the International Labor Organization jobless total -
which includes people looking for work but not claiming benefits -
fell by 86,000 between May and July compared to the first quarter
of the year.
</P>
<P>
The number of people in work in Britain rose to a record 27.4
million in three months to July, 54,000 higher than the previous
three months and almost 300,000 higher than the same period a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Union and industry leaders are urging the Bank of England not
to use the figures as another reason to raise interest rates.
</P>
