<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Old Northern Chinese Temple Gets Facelift </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Renovation work on
Longxing Temple, in Hebei Province's Zhengding County, has been
completed after two years.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is the largest of its kind since the
renovation of Lhasa's Potala Palace, cost 33 million yuan. The
funds came from the central and regional governments and
individuals.
</P>
<P>
The temple was built in the year 971. It has a 21.3 meter high
bronze Buddha that is considered to the largest built during the
period.
</P>
<P>
The building has been refurbished several times, most recently
in 1944. Several small halls were demolished during that
renovation work, greatly altering the original appearance of the
temple.
</P>
<P>
Field studies revealed some structural defects that were
seriously endangering the safety of the temple's cultural relics
and the bronze Buddha and the original appearance of the temple
needed to be restored. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
