<HEADLINE> Typhoon York Affects Southeastern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A strong storm, caused by
Typhoon York, has swept the coastal province of Fujian, causing
six deaths and serious flooding along the province's coastline.
</P>
<P>
More than 10,000 people there have been cut off by the floods,
according to the province's flood-fighting department. For the
past two days, the storm has brought heavy rain to Zhangzhou,
Xiamen, Quanzhou, Putian and Fuzhou and caused heavy flooding
there.
</P>
<P>
It forced the cancellation of flights from Changle
International Airport to Xiamen, Hong Kong, and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The province has various measures to ensure the safety of its
citizens and to try to keep damage to a minimum. Soldiers and
police in the province have been called in to help those areas hit
hardest by the storm and floodwaters. 
</P>
