<HEADLINE> Jiang's View Vital to APEC's Future Development: Deputy FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The six-point view on APEC's
future development presented by Chinese President Jiang Zemin at
the just-concluded informal meeting of the leaders of the Asia-
Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum will help the group
continue its sound development, a senior Chinese official said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Deputy Foreign Minister Yang Jiechi told reporters on
the special plane of Jiang, who is on his way back home from New
Zealand after paying a state visit to the country and attending
the APEC meeting on September 12-13.
</P>
<P>
"Jiang put forward important opinions on the future development
direction of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation, which has
helped the leadership meeting succeed and will contribute much to
APEC's healthy development," Yang said, referring to Jiang's
speech made at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Jiang called on APEC members to adhere to the
group's unique cooperation approach, its nature as an economic
forum and other vital principles which have led to the success of
the 10-year-old group.
</P>
<P>
In order for APEC to maintain its vitality and make greater
contributions to the regional and world economic prosperity, Jiang
also urged APEC members to do a good job in the following six
areas:
</P>
<P>
-- actively promote common economic prosperity in the Asian-
Pacific region;
</P>
<P>
-- actively deepen regional economic and technical cooperation
so as to lay a solid foundation for medium- and long-term
development of the region;
</P>
<P>
-- actively and steadily push forward the process of trade and
investment liberalization and promote a sound development of the
multilateral trading system;
</P>
<P>
-- actively strengthen cooperation in the international
financial field and accelerate the establishment of a new fair and
rational international financial order;
</P>
<P>
-- firmly adhere to the right development direction of APEC and
maintain the vigor and vitality of the organization;
</P>
<P>
-- actively press ahead with the mutually beneficial
cooperation among APEC members.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that Jiang pointed out the future development
direction of regional economic cooperation and that his appeals
have received "wide attention and praise" from other APEC members.
</P>
<P>
On the sideline of the APEC leaders' informal meeting, Jiang
and U.S. President Bill Clinton held talks and exchanged views on
bilateral relations and other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Hailing the official meeting as "positive and constructive,"
Yang said it is vital for improving the current Sino-U.S. ties.
</P>
</TEXT>
