<HEADLINE> Nardello Wins Eleventh Stage in Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Daniele Nardello of
Mapei took the 11th stage of the Tour of Spain cycle race on
Thursday, a 201-kilometer ride between Huesca and Pla de Beret.
</P>
<P>
Nardello, who lies 17 minutes behind overall race leader
Abraham Olano of Spain in the overall standings, took the lead
after breaking away with a group of some 20 riders. He clocked a
time of five hours one minute and 37 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Olano of Once retained the overall leader's golden jersey.
</P>
<P>
Friday's 12th stage, is 147.7-km between Sort and the ski
resort of Ordino-Aracalis in Andorra, and includes three grade one
climbs. 
