<HEADLINE> Canada Issues Millennium Stamps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Canada Post has issued a
collection of 68 postage stamps featuring business and cultural
achievements of Canadians for the millennium, the Ottawa Citizen
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An elite of 500 strong gathered at the Museum of Civilization
in Hull north of Ottawa late Wednesday for the launch of the
stamps, which are chosen for the 22,000 limited edition hardcover
books, the Millennium Collection.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Deputy Prime Minister Herb Gray was present at the
launching ceremony in his capacity as minister in charge of the
millennium Bureau of Canada.
</P>
<P>
Among the families to see their names in the millennium stamps
are food retailers and bakers the Weston clan, Joseph-Armand
Bombardier, the inventor of the Ski-Doo, Rose-Anna Vachon,
producer of Jos.Louis and Maywests snack cakes, and McCain Foods,
the family of French fries and Maple Leaf bacon, according to the
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
McCain Foods opened business in New Brunswick in 1957, when it
employed only 30 people. The employment has expanded to more than
16,000 ever since. The company is producing almost 350,000
kilograms of French fries an hour for the markets the world wide.
</P>
