<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Cartoon Book To Increase Ozone Layer Awareness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- To Commemorate International
Ozone Layer Day, the State Environmental Protection Administration
(SEPA) and Children's Center have provided cartoon books for
Beijing's pupils to increase their environmental protection
awareness.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yuqing, SEPA's vice-director, said that ozone-depleting
substances will still be around by 2050 even if ozone layer
protection measures are increased, so children are expected to act
as environmental guardians in the next century.
</P>
<P>
International Ozone Day was started by the United Nations in
1994 to draw people's attention to the ozone layer problem.
</P>
<P>
China is the biggest producer and user of substances that
destroy the ozone layer, according to Wang Gengchen of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences. SEPA's vice-director Wang said that the 11th
Meeting of participants at the Montreal Protocol on Substances
that Deplete the Ozone Layer will be held in Beijing from November
29 to December 3.
</P>
<P>
China has eliminated 30,000 tons of substances that destroy the
ozone layer and 10,000 tons of Freon will be taken out of
circulation by December 31, 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
