<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola to Learn Irrigation Expertise from Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luanda, September 16 (xinhua) -- Angola will reinforce its
cooperation with Israel in agriculture, particularly in
irrigation, said Angola's minister of agriculture and rural
development on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Gilberto Lutukuta was quoted by Angop news agency as saying
that such cooperation will help Angolan farmers in cultivation in
the dry and semi- dry areas in south and southwest Angola.
</P>
<P>
In the provinces of Huila, Namibe and Cunene, in south and
southwest Angola, where the rainfall is scarce, farmers need
techniques to fully utilize water, according to local analyst.
</P>
<P>
Israel, a thirsty country in the middle east, has advanced
agricultural techniques especially in dealing with drought and
desert areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
