<HEADLINE> Coach Ma's Runners Dominate 1,500m in Chinese City Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, China, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Famous coach Ma Junren's
disciples finished one-two in the women's 1,500-meter finals in
the fourth Chinese City Games here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Top favorite Lan Lixin, the world junior champion who clocked 4:
10.05 in France in July, 1998, broke away in the last 500 meters
to stand atop the podium in 4:11.62, as her Dalian teammate Wu
Qingdong finished second in 4:14.11.
</P>
<P>
Seven runners coached by Ma Junren, entered the field of the 12
competitors and wounded up six of the top seven spots as Tian
Xiaoxia of Chengdu, Sichuan province, became the sole woman to
break the otherwise clear sweep by the Dalian runners, who took
the bronze medal in 4:14.58.
</P>
<P>
"Our runners are a competitive group," said Lan Lixin, "Coach
Ma has told us prior to the finals to run for the gold medal by
displaying our strength along the track."
</P>
<P>
"And I will run for more medals in my specialities of the 5,
000m and 10,000m later," said 20-year-old budding star.
</P>
<P>
Ma Junren stole the limelight in the world track arena in 1993
when his women disciples took titles in the 1993 world
championships in Stuttgart, Germany with two games records.
</P>
<P>
In September, 1993, three world records were created by his
women runners, including Wang Junxia and Qu Yunxia, in the 1,500m,
3,000m and 10,000m races at the seventh Chinese National Games in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Hong Kong Special Adminstrative Region took its
first medal in the Games by finishing second in the men's 100
meters. 
</P>
