<HEADLINE> Beijing Forest Protection Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Legislation to better protect
forest resources was approved here today by the Standing Committee
of the Beijing Municipal People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The Regulation on the Protection of Beijing Forest Resources
accords with the Forest Law, and will take effect on November 1.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city's forest coverage was 41.22 percent of its
total area, as compared with only 1.3 percent in 1949. To better
implement the Forest Law, the Congress approved the regulation in
accordance with the area's special situation. It deals with forest
management, fires, pest prevention, logging, and other items.
</P>
<P>
It also calls for the establishment of forest funds to provide
more incentive for tree planting and forest management. 
