<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Sudan, Egypt to Join Hands in Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia will cooperate
with Sudan and Egypt in sharing and utilizing the water resources
of the four rivers rising in Ethiopia, the Ministry of Water
Resources Development said.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Herald Thursday quoted Mohammed Ahmed, an
engineer of the ministry, as saying that the joint project would
enable the three countries to effectively and equitably use the
rivers.
</P>
<P>
The three countries had established a committee in charge of
formulating the project at a meeting in Addis Ababa last May,
Mohammed said, adding Ethiopia is the chairman of the committee.
</P>
<P>
He said the project will be launched at a meeting in Khartoum,
Sudan, next month.
</P>
<P>
The four rivers are the Tekeze River, the Baro River, the Akobo
River and the Nile River. 
</P>
