<HEADLINE> Silver, Gold Prices Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Prices of both the precious
metals silver and gold dropped Thursday on the bullion market in
Mumbai (Bombay) due to weak overseas advice coupled with increased
arrival.
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness), after a steady start at 8,010
rupees (186.28 U.S. dollars) per kilogram, reacted down to close
at 7,980 rupees (185.58 U.S. dollars), showing a fall of 30 rupees
(0.70 U.S. dollar) over the last close of 8,010 rupees (186.28
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) declined by 35 rupees (0.81 U.S.
dollars) to 7,855 rupees (182.67 U.S. dollars) per kg from 7,890
rupees (183.49 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, standard gold showed a fresh fall of 10 rupees (0.23
U.S. dollar) at 4,080 rupees (94.88 U.S. dollars) per ten grams
from the last close of 4,090 rupees (95.11 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
