<HEADLINE> Survey Shows Basic Satisfaction with Telecommunication Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese customers are
basically satisfied with the country's telecommunication services,
according to a survey conducted by the information center under
the Ministry of Information Industry.
</P>
<P>
The survey covers some 100 companies offering mobile
communication, paging, and Internet services in China, and results
show that customers think most highly of the paging service, which
garnered an approval rate of 78.54 percent, according to the
survey. Mobile communication and Internet services received good
marks from 73.47 and 56.35 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Complaints about Internet service were mainly on insufficient
speed for surfing the Net, especially while browsing and
downloading, as well as the high cost of the service.
</P>
<P>
While the paging service appears quite satisfactory to most
customers, there are still complaints about mistakes in customers'
messages.
</P>
<P>
Qu Weizhi, vice minister of Information Industry, said there is
still much room for improvement in China's telecom industry,
although it has been on a fast track in recent years. 
