<HEADLINE> Share Prices Slump on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices fell sharply
on the Singapore Stock Market Thursday on weakness in regional
markets and overnight losses on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) lost 30.74 points to
end at 2,089.84 points in medium trading.
</P>
<P>
The day's volume totaled 281.48 million units valued at 459.34
million Singapore dollars (271.80 million U.S. dollars). Losers
led gainers by 218 to 67 with 165 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
IPC topped the volume list with 32.88 million shares
transacted. Mentor remained second with a turnover of 26.40
million shares. IPSCOM was the next with 19.92 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA and SIA 200 led the gainers of the day rising 20 cents each
to close at the same 16.40 Singapore dollars. Sunlight climbed 11
cents to finish at 1.23 Singapore dollars. UE picked up 7 cents to
end at 1.70 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, CityDev headed the descent of the day losing
55 cents to close at 8.75 Singapore dollars. CenProp and Seaview
each sank 50 cents to finish at 12.50 and 10.70 Singapore dollars
respectively. Bukit Sem shed 40 cents to end at 16.60 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the renewed concerns over a possible rise in U.S.
interest rates after the release of economic data on Wednesday
also dampened the market.
</P>
<P>
The expected 0.3 percent rise of the U.S. consumer price index
in August failed to calm fears that the U.S. economy is still
growing too strongly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
