<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- To mark the 50th anniversary
of the People's Republic of China, a grand exhibition of the
achievements of the past half century will open here next Monday
at the Beijing Exhibition Hall, a senior official announced today.
</P>
<P>
"This exhibition is an important part of the celebrations for
National Day in Beijing," said Wang Chunzheng, vice chairman of
the Preparatory Committee for the Exhibition, at a news conference
at the Great Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
"It has significant political meaning since among all the grand
anniversary activities, this will be the first to open and the
last to conclude," said Wang, also vice minister of the State
Development Planning Commission. The exhibition will be held from
September 20 to October 18.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is jointly sponsored by the commission, the
Publicity Department of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), the State Economic and Trade Commission, the
Ministry of Finance, the State Statistics Bureau, and Beijing
Municipality.
</P>
<P>
