<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading French newspapers on Thursday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Criticized for its lack of action facing the crisis in East
Timor, the United Nations adopted on Wednesday with unanimity a
resolution authorizing the sending of a multinational force to
Dili to restore order and peace. According to various sources, the
peacekeeping force, which will be manned by from 7,000 to 8,000
soldiers, will disembark in Timor this weekend from Australia.
</P>
<P>
-- In an interview with Liberation, the number three of the
Islamic Salvation Front of Algeria, Abdelkader Hachani, expressed
his reserve about the referendum of national reconciliation to be
held in the country on Thursday. He said that Algerians cannot
reconcile with each other unless the responsibility of everybody
in the seven-year violence is made clear.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- After seven years of violence perpetrated by armed Islamic
groups which has killed more than 100,000 people, the Algerians
are appealed on Thursday to vote on the law of "civil concord"
aimed at pardoning all the Islamists except those who have killed
and raped. The announcement of clemency which will end by January
13 has not attracted massively the armed groups, as only from 250
to 300 of their members have surrendered to the government so far.
</P>
<P>
-- After the green light given by the United Nations Security
Council, the soldiers of a multinational force are expected to
arrive at East Timor this weekend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
