<HEADLINE> Australia Sees Troops in East Timor by Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- An Australian-led
multinational security force would be in East Timor by Monday,
Australian Defense Minister John Moore said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Asked at a news conference when troops would be deployed, he
said: "Probably late this weekend or Monday."
</P>
<P>
Moore said France Thursday made a strong commitment to the
force, while support was still being sought from the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council Wednesday authorized a
multinational force to move into East Timor to restore peace and
security.
</P>
<P>
Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer had said Australia
was ready to lead the quick deployment of a multinational force
into East Timor. 
