<HEADLINE> China Hopes for Reinforced UN Role: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that the role of
the United Nations, especially its Security Council, would be
maintained and reinforced under the current international
situation, said Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Sun Yuxi at a
press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Sun made the remark when asked about China's expectations of
the forthcoming 54th Session of the UN General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
He said that the UN session is expected to focus on upholding
the existing norms guiding the international relations, tackling
the challenge of the economic globalization, advancing the
disarmament process and promoting international cooperation in the
area of human rights.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that during the session the parties concerned would
achieve positive results in the above-mentioned areas to enable
the UN to play a better role in international affairs, the
spokesman said. 
</P>
