<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Lower for Fifth Straight Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
Thursday closed lower for the fifth straight session, with banks
and retailers feeling most of the heat.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index ended near its low for the day at
2,904.8 points, down 33.3 points or 1.13 percent. The index has
now shed more than 100 points since last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index took a caning, falling 65.9 points or
1.31 percent to 4,980.2, while the all resources slipped only 4.2
points or 0.32 percent to 1,299.3.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector led the way down in the stock market, losing
99.7 points, or 1.63 percent, to 6,006.7.
</P>
