<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Australian Prime Minister
John Howard Thursday said he did not pay much regard to
Indonesia's decision to scrap a four-year-old security treaty
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Australian government officials said the Australia-Indonesia
security treaty, signed in December 1995, was canceled by the
Indonesian government on Thursday.
</P>
