recent months -- we never saw it as being the solution to all the
problems of the relationship as the former government did," Howard
told Australia's 10 TV network.
</P>
<P>
"So I don't pay too much regard, and I'm not particularly
surprised by or concerned about this decision," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the bilateral relationship with Indonesia was under
strain, but he was confident it could be repaired. 
