their tickets for other sessions in view of the heavy number of
applicants.
</P>
<P>
IOC president Juan Antonio Samaranch had said in Lausanne that
members of the public would be entitled to get their money back if
they bought seats to events that had been rescheduled.
</P>
<P>
"I think it is a gesture we have to make to show we are really
co-operating with the organizing committee in Sydney," he said.
</P>
<P>
IOC had rearranged 11 track and field finals for the 2000 Games
even though tickets for the events had already gone on sale,
Olympics minister Michael Knight announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The changes were made after the International Amateur Athletics
Federation asked for rest days between heats and finals for middle
and long distance races. 
