<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Sector Employs More People in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The figure shows that there are a total of 1.119 million urban
laborers in the province, 215,700 of whom are working for state-
owned enterprises and 258,200 for the private sector.
</P>
<P>
This increase is attributed to the structural reform in state-
owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The fact that more and more people have changed their thinking
away from the concept of the "iron rice bowl," a guaranteed state
job for life, is another reason for the surge.
</P>
<P>
The private economy in China has been growing very fast since
the country began opening to the outside world in 1978, and ever
more people have begun working in the private sector, as many
laid-off workers from state-owned enterprises joined private
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
According to the State Administration for Industry and Commerce,
the number of private enterprises in China reached 1.28 million in
June this year, 80,000 more than at end of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
