<HEADLINE> Cargo Vessel Found Sinking Outside HK Waters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A river trade cargo vessel
was found sinking outside Hong Kong waters about seven nautical
miles west of Lantau Island amid the approaching of Typhoon York,
according to a government press release.
</P>
<P>
All of the five persons on board were airlifted by the
government Flying Service and being transferred to hospital for
observation around 11:30 Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
Hurricane Signal No. 10, which was the most serious in the past
16 years in Hong Kong, is still hoisted.
</P>
<P>
All courts, banks and schools remain closed. Clinics run by the
Department of Health and the Hospital Authority are closed, but
Accident and Emergency services at hospitals remain normal.
</P>
