<HEADLINE> More Flights Canceled in Hong Kong Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of 68 flights have
been canceled, 95 flights delayed and 12 flights diverted up to 1:
00 p.m. Thursday due to the attack of Typhoon York, the Airport
Authority said.
</P>
<P>
The airport remains open, but its north runway was closed at 8:
30 a.m. The Airport Express is running at 15-minute intervals.
</P>
<P>
Most of airlines have stopped check-in temporarily and have
opened hotlines for inquiry by passengers.
</P>
<P>
A LPG tanker and a container vessel were drifted by strong
winds toward the north of the airport. The LPG tanker has been
towed away from Hong Kong waters. Neither casualties nor gas
leakage were reported. 
</P>
