<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 17 Lebanese Pro-Israeli Militiamen Convicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon's Military Tribunal
Wednesday night gave 17 former pro-Israeli militiamen prison terms
ranging from two to 18 months for collaboration with Israel.
</P>
<P>
So far, 151 former members of the Israeli-allied South Lebanon
Army (SLA) have stood trial since the militia withdrew in June
from the Jezzine area, a predominantly Christian town just outside
the security zone.
</P>
<P>
The convicts are among the 220 militiamen who voluntarily
surrendered to the authorities after the SLA withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
Most of the militiamen put on trial have got light sentences
except three senior SLA officials, with two getting 15 years in
prison and a third receiving seven years.
</P>
<P>
The 2,500-strong SLA, formed in 1985 when Israel set up a
security zone in south Lebanon with a claimed aim of protecting
its north from Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks, was
trained and armed by Israel to help patrol the occupied border
strip.
</P>
<P>
It had been policing Jezzine for the past 14 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman on Reunification of Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Jing Shuping, vice-chairman
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said the greatest wish for people
of his generation is to witness the country's prosperity and
reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Jing, who is in his 80s, said he hopes to see the reunification
of the two sides of the Taiwan Straits in his lifetime. "The
reunification of the motherland will be a high point for the whole
Chinese nation," he said.
</P>
<P>
The reunification of the motherland is not only a major event
for the country, Jing said, it is also important to his family, as
his younger brother lives in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Jing reunited with his brother in Hong Kong in the 1980s after
decades of separation.
</P>
<P>
Having led a delegation to Taiwan in 1996, Jing said the gap
between the people across the straits has been narrowed in terms
of people's living standards after 20 years' implementation of the
reform and opening-up policy.
</P>
<P>
He believes that the "one country, two systems" policy is
reasonable for Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He said over 40,000 Taiwan companies have investment in inland
areas and the cross-straits import and export volume has reached
over 20 billion U.S. dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
The early realization of direct exchanges of mail delivery,
trade and air and shipping services will benefit people on both
sides of the Taiwan Straits, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Multinationals Positive About Investing in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- "Shenyang, as one important
heavy industrial base in China, and the traffic hinge connecting
north and northeast China, is a large market of great potential,"
said Frank A. Ogden, executive vice president of General Motors
China Operations, at the recent Shenyang 99' Transnationals Forum.
</P>
<P>
GM entered the Chinese market in 1991 when they signed a
contract of cooperation with the Jinbei Auto Company.
</P>
<P>
Business was not as positive then as now, as the Chinese
partner had finance difficulties. However, they finally signed a
contract setting up a joint venture on June 22, 1998, with 230
million U.S. dollars, dividing the investment and the share in
half.
</P>
<P>
"The foreign investment environment has improved a lot in the
past few years," said Mr. Ogden who has witnessed great changes in
this field during his days in China. The GM Chevrolet is expected
to go into production in China in 2001, with output reaching 30,
000 vehicles for the first phase, and 50,000 in the second phase.
</P>
<P>
Many managers of multinational corporations share a similar
opinion when asked about their reasons for investing in northeast
China.
</P>
<P>
"We have confidence that high-quality tires will have good
sales in northeast China, " said Mr. Monteil, president of the
Michelin Shenyang Tire Co. Ltd. France's Michelin began its
investment in the city in December 1995.
</P>
<P>
Along with this joint venture, Michelin has set up three others
in the past few years because of the Shenyang's improved
investment environment and great market potential.
</P>
<P>
The company now has invested a total of 120 million U.S.
dollars in the city, and its products have entered markets in
Europe, North America, Asia, and Oceania, with tire exports
accounting for 80 percent of the output, and export value over 22
million U.S. dollars last year, said Mr. Monteil.
</P>
<P>
" We thought twice before deciding on a site in China for our
color TV factory," said general manager of LG Electronics (
Shenyang) Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
"It is true that south China is much further along in economic
development, but Shenyang has the advantage of good location,
abundant resources, and convenient traffic," he added.
</P>
<P>
The total investment of LG Electronics of the Republic of Korea
topped 660 million U.S. dollars by the end of 1998, and is
expected to reach 2 billion U.S. dollars by the year 2005,
according to the general manager. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flooding Reported in Hong Kong Amid Typhoon Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of 33 cases of
flooding have been recorded when Typhoon York attacked Hong Kong
Thursday morning, according to a government press release.
</P>
<P>
There have been 126 reports of trees being uprooted, of which
111 are in the New Territories and 15 in the urban area.
</P>
<P>
Sections of about 40 roads remain closed because of dangerous
scaffolding or fallen trees.
</P>
<P>
Electricity supplied by overhead lines in some remote villages
was interrupted by adverse weather. Repair work is being arranged
wherever possible.
</P>
<P>
The Mass Transit Railway is running a limited service. All
services of public buses, ferries, trams, the Light Rail Transit
and the Kowloon-Canton Railway have been suspended. 
</P>
