<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Internet continues to
be the fastest growing medium in India.
</P>
<P>
According to the Indian Readership Survey 1999, as of June 30,
there were 1.527 million Internet users in the country.
</P>
<P>
On the reach of media in rural and urban areas, it said that
while newspapers reached 32.9 percent of the population,
television reached 47.2 percent, radio 17.7 percent and cinema
12.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Although television's reach has increased across all town
classes, it is not very high.
</P>
