meaning that inflation has risen 0.4 percent so far this year, the
lowest figure for the first eight months of any year since 1967.
</P>
<P>
It is also the first time in 1999 that the inflation total is
above zero. Despite the low inflation rate thus far in 1999,
experts expect the final figure to hover around 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Ha'aretz:
</P>
<P>
-- Israel's army Chief of Staff Shaul Mofaz said in an
interview with Ha'aretz that Israel and the Palestinians are not
likely to meet Prime Minister Ehud Barak's goal of reaching a
final-status agreement in one year.
</P>
<P>
He warned that "a fifty-year conflict cannot be resolved within
a year or two," saying that the major problems are still ahead of
both sides. "So the time frame is the big question."
</P>
<P>
Ma'ariv:
</P>
<P>
-- The health of Syrian President Hafez Assad is
deteriorating. Western diplomats meeting him recently said he was
disoriented in talks and could not complete his thoughts and
sentences clearly.
</P>
<P>
Yediot Aharonot:
</P>
<P>
-- Former Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is obstructing the
police investigation over charges that he and his wife, Sara,
received bribes and misused public funds during his three-year
term of office.
</P>
<P>
He and Sara were questioned separately by police for more than
eight hours Wednesday and will possibly be summoned for
questioning again. 
