<HEADLINE> Myanmar Builds 256 Dams in 51 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar built a total of 256
dams up to August this year since 1948 when the country regained
independence with a total of 1.146 million hectares of land
irrigated, said Myanmar leader Senior-General Than Shwe.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an annual general meeting of the Union Solidarity
Development Association here Wednesday, Than Shwe, chairman of the
Myanmar State Peace and Development Council, said 65 dams were
built between 1948 and fiscal 1961-62, irrigating more than
344,250 hectares. 91 dams were built from 1962-63 to 1988-89,
irrigating more than 202,500 hectares of land and 100 others built
from 1988-89 to August 1999, irrigating more than 599,400
hectares.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that there are 13 dams under construction for the
bringing 392,850 hectares more of land under irrigation. He added
that the country is initiating 37 other irrigating projects,
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
There are 18.22 million hectares of cultivable land in Myanmar,
of which only 9.31 million hectares are being used for
agricultural purpose.
</P>
<P>
The country is making efforts to reclaim the remaining 8.91
million hectares of land, laying down a strategy for the
agricultural sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
