<HEADLINE> Seven Killed in U.S. Texas Church Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed
and at least eight others wounded when a gunman opened fire in a
church during a youth service on Wednesday night in Fort Worth in
Texas State, the United States, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
A Fort Worth Police Department spokesman said the man, in his
30s and dressed in black, killed three adults and three teenagers
before killing himself.
</P>
<P>
Eight more were hospitalized, some in crucial condition, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Police said they did not know the motive of the shooting yet,
nor the gunman's identity.
</P>
<P>
Some 150 young people were attending a prayer service and
concert for youths when the shooting took place. 
</P>
