<HEADLINE> 18 Persons Injured in Typhoon Attacks in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen persons were
admitted to hospitals as a result of storm-related injuries and
three of them have already been discharged after treatment, the
Hong Kong government said in a press release Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A man was reported missing from a capsized sampan off Yim Tin
Tsai in Tai Po, the New Territories of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has almost come to a standstill as Hurricane Signal
No. 10 remains hoisted, meaning that winds with a mean speed of
118 kilometers per hour or more are expected.
</P>
<P>
Hurricane Signal No. 10 was hoisted at 6:45 a.m. Thursday, for
the first time in 16 years.
</P>
<P>
At 11:00 a.m., Typhoon York was centered about 25 kilometers
south-southwest of the Hong Kong Observatory and is forecast to
move west-northwest at about 15 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The Home Affairs Department of Hong Kong has opened 29
temporary shelters and so far 131 people have sought refuge there.
</P>
