<HEADLINE> Public Transport Services Suspended Due to Typhoon Attack in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- All services of public
buses, ferries, trams, Light Rail Transit and Kowloon-Canton
Railway have been suspended due to the attack of Typhoon York in
Hong Kong Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Mass Transit Railway is running a limited service and 11
roads have been so far closed owing to dangerous scaffolding or
fallen trees.
</P>
<P>
The north runway of the airport was closed at 8:30 a.m. while
15 flights have been canceled, 55 delayed and 11 diverted.
</P>
<P>
Geotechnical Engineering Office staff are providing advice on
the sites where flooding is reported.
</P>
<P>
Clinics run by the Department of Health and the Hospital
Authority are closed, but accident and emergency services at
hospitals remain normal.
</P>
<P>
At 11:00 a.m., Typhoon York was centered about 25 kilometers
south-southwest of the Hong Kong Observatory and is forecast to
move west-northwest at about 15 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The Hurricane Signal No. 10 was hoisted at 6:45 a.m. Thursday,
meaning that winds with a mean speed of 118 kilometers per hour or
more are expected. The Hurricane Signal No. 10 was last hoisted in
Hong Kong in 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
