<HEADLINE> Exit Poll Sees BJP Ahead in India's Lok Sabha Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Exit polls conducted by
media organization Doordarshan on the first two phases of the Lok
Sabha elections, released Thursday, projected a comfortable lead
for the BJP-led National Democratic Alliance (NDA).
</P>
<P>
Of the 268 parliamentary seats for which voting has been
completed, the BJP and its allies were set to win 145 seats, a
gain of 28 from last Lok Sabha polls and the Congress party and
its allies were likely to take 105, only two fewer than last time.
</P>
<P>
In the 545-seat Lok Sabha, the coalition led by BJP would
require a majority of 272 seats to form a government.
</P>
<P>
The polls suggested that the biggest losers in the first phases
of the elections were smaller parties which are not part of the
rainbow coalition put together by the BJP and do not come under
the Congress umbrella.
</P>
<P>
The NDA tally has gone up with the BJP strength rising
significantly in Maharashtra, Rajasthan and Haryana. BJP and
allies gained as many as 19 seats in Maharashtra, six in Rajasthan
and five in Haryana.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the Election Commission withdrew its controversial
guidelines banning the publication and telecast of opinion and
exit polls during the election following the Supreme Court ruling
that the commission had no power to issue such an order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
