<HEADLINE> Exiled Paraguayan General Warned Not to Perform Political Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Argentine government
Wednesday warned exiled Paraguayan ex-general Lino Oviedo not to
plan or participate in political activities within the country.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Carlos Corach said that Argentina would
defend his right to asylum, but that it was also "inflexible" in
its decision to not permit Oviedo to participate in political
activities within the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the opposition alliance, Oviedo held a political
meeting last Saturday in Argentina, which was attended by dozens
of his followers.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine government's warning to Oviedo was made in
response to the political opposition's appeal to the Supreme
Court to have Argentina's denial of Paraguay's right of
extradition in the Oviedo case declared unconstitutional.
</P>
<P>
Oviedo came to Argentina for asylum on March 29. He was accused
of instigating the assassination of Paraguayan Vice-President Luis
Maria Argana on March 23. For that reason the Paraguayan justice
system has requested his extradition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
