<HEADLINE> Flights Suspended Due to Typhoon Attacks in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Tropical Typhoon York that
is approaching Hong Kong forced the cancellation and delay of a
dozen of flights at the Hong Kong Airport Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The airport has shut down the northern runway and major
airlines ceased to check in passengers due to the flight delay.
</P>
<P>
Cathay Pacific Airways says it will not have flight incoming or
departing in the morning and eight incoming flights have been
diverted to Taipei and Manila.
</P>
<P>
Major airlines have opened hotlines for inquiries by passengers,
many of whom are now stranded at the airport and waiting for the
latest flight information.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Observatory early Thursday morning hoisted
Hurricane Signal No. 10, for the first time in Hong Kong since
1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
