<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0311 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ottey Positive on Second Sample Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Jamaica's world champion
Merlene Ottey is entitled to a hearing after her second sample
doping test returned positive.
</P>
<P>
The Jamaican Amateur Athletic Association (JAAA) said in
Kingston on Wednesday that the International Amateur Athletic
Federation (IAAF) had advised that "the 'B' sample from Ottey has
also tested positive."
</P>
<P>
Under IAAF rules, the former 200 meters world champion was
entitled to a hearing by the IAAF and a panel would be set up to
hear the evidence to make a decision, according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The hearing is expected to take place at the end of November
this year in order to "afford her a reasonable time to prepare",
it added.
</P>
<P>
Ottey's management company revealed on August 18 that the 39-
year-old sprinter had tested positive for the banned steroid
nandrolone at a grand prix meeting in Lucerne, Switzerland, on
July 5.
</P>
<P>
Ottey, who has 14 world championship medals to her name, has
vowed to prove her innocence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
