<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chelsea Complete English Goalless Draw in Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Chelsea, which made its debut
at the Champions League, completed an English goalless draw with
rivals in the opening group phase on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The club, which finished third in the English Premier League
last season, played to a 0-0 draw with AC Milan at Stamford Bridge
in an absorbing match in which both teams unluckily hit the
woodwork.
</P>
<P>
Italian Gianfranco Zola hit Milan's post midway through the
second half, before Leonardo rattled Chelsea's crossbar soon after
with a left-foot, 25-meter shot.
</P>
<P>
All three English clubs in the Champions League drew 0-0 after
holders Manchester United finished goalless with Croatia Zagreb
and Arsenal were held by Fiorentina on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
There was more excitement in the other Group H match in
Istanbul where Hertha Berlin raced into a 2-0 lead after only 12
minutes with goals from Michael Preetz at the 10th minute and
Daruisz Wosz two minutes later.
</P>
<P>
But Galatasaray, inspired by their fanatical fans in the Ali
Sami Yen Stadium, fought back for a point with a 21st minute goal
from Hakan Sukur and an 89th minute penalty from Gheorghe Hagi.
Kostas Konstatinidis of Hertha was shown the red card eight
minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
Last season's beaten finalists Bayern Munich began their
Champions League campaign with a hard-fought 2-1 victory over PSV
Eindhoven in their opening Group F match.
</P>
<P>
Bayern, lost to Manchester United in the emotional finishing
seconds of last season's final, won with two goals from Paulo
Sergio after 11 and 69 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Eindhoven's Dmitri Khokhlov scored for the Dutch side at the
59th minute and their miserable evening ended with Mark van Bommel
being sent off for a second bookable offense just before the end.
</P>
<P>
In the other Group F match Valencia beat Scottish champions
Rangers 2-0 with Kily Gonzalez scoring both goals for the home
side in an eight-minute spell midway through the second half.
</P>
<P>
Following the opening night of Champions League action on
Tuesday in Groups A-D, the most dramatic match on Wednesday was in
Piraeus where Olympiakos and Real Madrid traded the lead in their
Group E Match before settling for a 3-3 draw.
</P>
<P>
Olympiakos appeared to be heading for a stunning 3-2 victory
over the former European champions when Zlatko Zahovic put them
ahead after 67 minutes to the delight of the 80,000 home fans.
</P>
<P>
But Real struck back with an equaliser from Raul 10 minutes
from time.
</P>
<P>
The Greek side, crushed 5-1 by Madrid in the same competition
two seasons ago, also scored through Brazilian Giovanni at the
10th and 64th minutes. Madrid's earlier goals were scored by
Savio at the 24th minute and Roberto Carlos (32nd).
</P>
<P>
In other Group E action, Deco scored an 88th minute winner for
Porto against Norwegians Molde.
</P>
<P>
In Group G Andrei Tikhonov scored all three Spartak Moscow
goals -- two from the spot -- as they beat Willem II Tilburg 3-1
in the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The other match in the group between Sparta Prague and
Girondins Bordeaux ended in a 0-0 draw after Sparta captain Horst
Siegl missed a 55th minute penalty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
