<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet's Weather Good For Farming And Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The favorable climate in the
Tibet Autonomous Region this summer has provided a good harvest
for farmers and herders and has been good for the fledgling
tourism industry
</P>
<P>
In July and August, while heatwaves hit much of China,
including Beijing, the capital, Tibet, in southwest China, was
having more rainfall and cooler weather than normal. Local
meteorologists and agronomists attribute this to the La Nina
effect and lower temperatures in the Bay of Bengal, where warm,
wet fronts originated and headed north to meet the cold air on the
Tibet-Qinghai Plateau.
</P>
<P>
And, the efforts to bring more new technology to herding and
farming have paid off, analysts say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
