<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock
Exchange on Wednesday closed up with benchmark IPC index
increasing 0.39 points or 0.01 percent, at 4,970.24 points.
</P>
<P>
Opeartors exchanged 81.737 million shares worth some 115.679
million dollars aginst 44.598 million shares for an amount of some
84.783 million dollars on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, peso, mainted unchanged at 9.50 to one
dollar for sale and 9.15 for purchase in the Bank of Mexico.
</P>
