<HEADLINE> Vialli Proud of Chelsea's Draw with AC Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Chelsea manager Gianluca
Vialli was a proud man as his club matched AC Milan for quality in
their Champions League opener at Stamford Bridge on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gianfranco Zola came within inches of bagging a winner for
Chelsea when he hit the post, though Milan almost stole victory
when Brazilian star Leonardo struck the bar with five minutes
remaining.
</P>
<P>
"I am very proud of my players because to play so well against
a team like AC Milan is something to be proud of," said Vialli
after the match finished goalless.
</P>
<P>
"We showed we can compete with everybody, we are good enough to
be in the Champions League.
</P>
<P>
"It's not going to be easy, it's going to be difficult but we
started quite well with one point."
</P>
<P>
Vialli was especially pleased with Chelsea's first-half display,
when the Blues dominated the Italian giants.
</P>
<P>
"In the second half it was more difficult - we got tired and
they played better," he said. "We had a few chances, we hit the
post -but they hit the bar with five minutes to go.
</P>
<P>
"It is a shame we didn't score and obviously we regret that a
little bit but in our first match I think we did very well," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
