<HEADLINE> Argentine Stock Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index
of the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange closed down 0.53 percent at 525.
27 points on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 30.366 million U.S. dollars against 34.681
million dollars on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the continuing decline of the stock was
influenced by the fall of dow Jones index in Wall street.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest increased to 8.40 percent
from 7.65 percent in the 24-hour term. The parity of the peso
against the dollar remained unchanged at 0.997 for purchase and 1.
002 for sale. 
</P>
