<HEADLINE> IAA Motor Show Opens in Frankfurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FRANKFURT, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Frankfurt International
Motor Show (IAA), one of the world's major motor shows, opens its
doors Thursday in Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
About 1,200 exhibitors from 44 different countries are
preparing to wow the crowds with their latest designs and models
at a time when the global auto industry is still zooming along in
the fast track.
</P>
<P>
With a total of 225,000 square meters of exhibition space,
cars and special vehicles take up 12 halls, with additional halls
set aside for motor bikes and scooters, caravans, trailers and
model cars.
</P>
<P>
Another six halls house the latest innovations in maintenance
equipment and car parts. There is also a special area where
visitors can test drive the latest models.
</P>
<P>
A total of 51 brand new models will be unveiled at the fair,
which will end on September 26.
</P>
<P>
The IAA, the third major motor show this year after Detroit
and Geneva, is organized by the German auto industry association
VDA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
