<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela Reaffirms Stance to Cut Crude Oil Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Hugo
Chavez on Wednesday reaffirmed his country's stance to cut crude
oil production.
</P>
<P>
"We are not interested in increasing our production", said
Chavez, adding that Venezuela would hold the agreement of cutting
production which it has with Mexico and other OPEC members.
</P>
<P>
Chavez, who advocates stability in the world-wide petroleum
market, observed that the fluctuation of price creates distortions
in the market of producing countries as well as in the consumer
countries.
</P>
<P>
The independent oil exporters and OPEC members agreed on April
1 to cut crude production by 2.1 million barrels per day for a
year in order to recuperate the petroleum prices in the world
markets.
</P>
<P>
Chavez insisted that his government should propose to OPEC to
adopt a floatation band to realize higher stability of the
petroleum prices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
