<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0334 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Global Broadband Satellite Revenue to Expand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Worldwide broadband
satellite revenues will increase from 230 million U.S. dollars
this year to 37 billion dollars in 2008, according to an analysis
released Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the total revenue, residential service will contribute the
majority, with almost 22 billion dollars in 2008, according to a
report from Pioneer Consulting, a U.S. firm specializing in global
high-speed telecommunications network market research.
</P>
<P>
Total revenues of both business and residential services will
double between 2001 and 2002, from 3 billion dollars to 6 billion
dollars, and jump again from 16 billion dollars to 31 billion
dollars between 2004 and 2007.
</P>
<P>
According to the market research firm, North America will be
the largest market for broadband service, due to the strong desire
for higher bandwidth by residential users and the willingness of
business users to try new access technologies.
</P>
<P>
Asia will be second in revenue at the end of the forecast
period, ahead of Europe, due to the predicted popularity of
residential broadband satellite access. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
