<DOCNO> XIE19990916.0335 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China's Port City Active in Trade Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Port, the largest
man-made port in north China and also the gateway to the Chinese
capital, has in the past 15 years opened over 60 international
navigation lines and set up trade relationships with more than 300
ports in some 160 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
It has also forged friendly ties with Japan's Tokyo and Kobe
ports, Philadelphia in the United States, Australia's Melbourne,
France's Marseilles, the Netherlands' Amsterdam, the Inchon Port
of the Republic of Korea, and Belgium's Bruges.
</P>
<P>
And among the 43 joint ventures in the port area, the Port of
Tianjin Commercial Bonded Warehousing and Service Co. Ltd. has
been most successful. A cooperative venture with the Royal
Nedlloyd Group N.V. Rotterdam, the Netherlands, it is the first
commerce-oriented warehousing firm in China.
</P>
<P>
The firm, offering storage services and simple processing to
the automobile, clothing, and chemical materials both for import
and export, operates under a management structure similar to
foreign tax-free ports or free trade zones.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, some 2,000 enterprises with a total investment of 3
billion U.S. dollars have settled in the Tianjin Free Trade Zone
since its establishment in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Half of the port's 43 joint ventures, dealing mainly in storage,
international trade, and raw materials processing on client demand,
have also chosen the zone for its preferential policies.
</P>
<P>
The Xingang area, south of the port, where the Free Trade Zone
is located, is of extreme importance to the port's prospects in
the 21st century, said officials in charge of port affairs
administration.
</P>
<P>
As a result, a dozen foreign firms have in the last three years
invested in the five-sq km developed area of Xingang, and
multinationals like Esso, Mobile, and Shell have already set up
their branches or agencies there, added the officials.
</P>
<P>
Among the first 14 coastal cities approved by the State Council
to be open to foreign countries in 1984, Tianjin is the most
highly favored.  
</P>
</TEXT>
