<HEADLINE> Spain Supports Urgent UN Intervention in East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Spanish Senate on
Wednesday approved unanimously a declaration of supporting the UN
urgent intervention in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the international force will be to end the
violations of the most elemental human rights and also to uphold
the results of the referendum on independence.
</P>
<P>
In the declaration, the Senate showed it was convinced that "it
is necessary to respect the result of the democratic
consultation", in which the population of Timor showed "their
unequivocal will to govern themselves" in the face of the
generalized violence being experienced in the zone.
</P>
<P>
They request the UN to exercise its obligation to protect the
population, with the help of the whole international community and
that the intervention should be urgent "because Timor is enduring
new excesses and persecutions".
</P>
<P>
The Senate urged the UN to act with the necessary speed to end
the suffering of the population of East Timor as soon as possible,
and to re-establish the popular will of the people to live in
peace and liberty. 
</P>
