<HEADLINE> Britain Sees Doubling of Online Shopping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Online shopping has doubled in
the past year in Britain, said an annual survey carried out by
Which?Online, the Internet arm of UK Consumers' Association.
</P>
<P>
The survey of 2,000 people across Britain showed that 58
percent of those who had been online for more than two years had
bought something.
</P>
<P>
It also found books, flights and holidays have taken over from
computer hardware and software as the most popular products being
sold.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that 10 million people in Britain, about
one-sixth of the population, are now using the Internet. But it
appears that the high cost of phone calls continues to limit the
amount of time the surfers spent online.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that three-quarters of users surf the
Internet for five hours or less a week and visit on average 13
websites a week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
